FBIS3-30574 "dreeu025_k_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 CROATIA Shell With `Special Fuse' Used in Sarajevo LD0602222394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 6 Feb 94 LD0602222394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] A convention of military psychologists entitled The Treatment of Combat Stress Reactions, which will take place over the next two days chaired by Warren Dale, the director of the San Francisco trauma program, opened this evening at the Croatian military academy. [passage omitted] In his speech, General Janko Bobetko, the chief of general staff of the Croatian Army, mentioned yesterday's massacre in Sarajevo. [Begin Bobetko recording] The attack was very organized, with propaganda immediately saying that it was one shell and that it was by chance. This is not true. It was a shell with a special fuse, that under an angle of 60 degrees has an impact within a 60-90 meter radius, causing 70-80 percent mortal injuries. It can be fired from a distance of three to four kilometers. [end recording] [passage omitted]
